s($,"b5_","aEj",()=>{var q="Why learning languages is useful",p="It is becoming increasingly useful",o="Because English is used in many international companies",n="To speak to online friends from different countries",m="Different cultures and traditions",l="memory, confidence, and problem-solving skills",k=t.s,j=t.N,i=t.K,h=t.Mq,g=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 1: Why Do People Learn Languages?","backButtonText","Back to Unit 1","title","Why Do People Learn Languages?","lessonId","unit1_lesson1","unitTitle","Unit 1","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit1_lesson1_grammar.mp4","completionText",u.O,"inputType","reading","imagePath","assets/images/unit1_lesson1.png","input","People learn languages for many different reasons. Some people learn English because they need it for work, while others learn it to travel or study in another country. Today, English is used in many international companies, airports, hotels, and universities around the world. Because of this, many people believe that learning English can create new opportunities in life.\n\nLanguages also help people communicate with others. Some teenagers learn languages so they can speak to online friends from different countries. Others enjoy watching films, listening to music, or playing games in another language. Learning a language can also help people understand different cultures and traditions better.\n\nAlthough learning a language can sometimes be difficult, many learners say it is rewarding. Students often feel proud when they can successfully understand a song, read a text, or have a conversation in another language. Teachers believe that language learning also improves memory, confidence, and problem-solving skills.\n\nIn today\u2019s connected world, speaking more than one language is becoming increasingly useful. Whether people learn languages for work, travel, education, or communication, language learning helps people connect with the wider world.","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main idea of the text?","options",A.b(["How to become a teacher",q,"Why schools are difficult","How to travel around the world"],k),"answer",q],j,i),A.f(["question","Which language does the text mainly discuss?","options",A.b(["Spanish","Chinese","English","French"],k),"answer","English"],j,i),A.f(["question","What does the writer say about learning languages today?","options",A.b(["Only children should learn languages","Most people dislike language learning",p,"It is becoming less important"],k),"answer",p],j,i)],h),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","opportunities","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","chances to do something good or successful"],j,j),A.f(["word","communicate","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","to share information, thoughts, or feelings with others"],j,j),A.f(["word","traditions","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","beliefs or ways of doing things that are passed from one generation to another"],j,j),A.f(["word","rewarding","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","making you feel happy or satisfied because something is worthwhile"],j,j),A.f(["word","successfully","partOfSpeech","adv","meaning","in a good or effective way"],j,j),A.f(["word","confidence","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the feeling of believing in yourself"],j,j),A.f(["word","increasingly","partOfSpeech","adv","meaning","more and more over time"],j,j),A.f(["word","connect","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","to join or communicate with people"],j,j)],g),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Speaking clearly can help students ______ with people from other countries.","options",A.b(["traditions","confidence","communicate","rewarding"],k),"answer","communicate"],j,i),A.f(["sentence","Many schools are ______ using technology in the classroom.","options",A.b(["successfully","confidence","connect","increasingly"],k),"answer","increasingly"],j,i),A.f(["sentence","Learning a new skill can be difficult, but it is often very ______.","options",A.b(["traditions","communicate","rewarding","opportunities"],k),"answer","rewarding"],j,i),A.f(["sentence","Students feel more ______ when they practise speaking English every day.","options",A.b(["connect","successfully","confidence","traditions"],k),"answer","confidence"],j,i),A.f(["sentence","Festivals are important ______ in many cultures around the world.","options",A.b(["opportunities","communicate","rewarding","traditions"],k),"answer","traditions"],j,i),A.f(["sentence","Good exam results can create new ______ for young people.","options",A.b(["confidence","opportunities","successfully","connect"],k),"answer","opportunities"],j,i),A.f(["sentence","Mei answered all the questions ______ during the interview.","options",A.b(["rewarding","traditions","communicate","successfully"],k),"answer","successfully"],j,i),A.f(["sentence","Social media allows teenagers to ______ with friends around the world.","options",A.b(["confidence","connect","opportunities","increasingly"],k),"answer","connect"],j,i)],h),"grammar",A.f(["title","Question Words","summary",A.f(["grammarPoint","Question Words","use","We use question words to ask for information.","form","Who + verb... ?\nWhat + auxiliary + subject + verb... ?\nWhere + auxiliary + subject + verb ... ?","examples",A.b(["Who lives in Melbourne?","Where is English used?","What does language learning improve?"],k),"remember","Question words help us learn new information."],j,i),"example",A.f(["sentence","People learn languages for work and travel.","answer","Why do people learn languages?"],j,j),"instruction","Complete each question with the correct question word.","practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence","______ is English used?","question","English is used in airports and hotels.","answer","Where"],j,j),A.f(["sentence","______ do some teenagers want to speak to?","question","Teenagers want to speak to online friends.","answer","Who"],j,j),A.f(["sentence","______ does language learning improve?","question",u.P,"answer","What"],j,j),A.f(["sentence","______ is becoming increasingly useful?","question","Speaking more than one language is becoming increasingly useful.","answer","What"],j,j),A.f(["sentence","______ father speaks Cantonese and English?","question","Kelly\u2019s father speaks Cantonese and English.","answer","Whose"],j,j)],g)],j,i),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","Why do some people learn English for work?","options",A.b(["Because English is easier than other languages",o,"Because English has fewer grammar rules","Because English is only spoken in Europe"],k),"answer",o],j,i),A.f(["question","Why do some teenagers learn languages?","options",A.b(["To avoid homework","To become famous online",n,"To stop using technology"],k),"answer",n],j,i),A.f(["question","What can learning a language help people understand better?","options",A.b(["Science and maths","Computer programming",m,"Sports competitions"],k),"answer",m],j,i),A.f(["question","How do students often feel when they successfully use another language?","options",A.b(["Confused","Angry","Bored","Proud"],k),"answer","Proud"],j,i),A.f(["question","According to teachers, language learning improves:","options",A.b(["speed and fitness",l,"drawing and painting skills","muscle strength"],k),"answer",l],j,i)],h),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What do some people need English for?","answer","work","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["their job","jobs","employment","working"],k)],j,i),A.f(["question","What do some learners enjoy watching in another language?","answer","films","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["film","movies","movie"],k)],j,i),A.f(["question","What do students sometimes read in another language?","answer","a text","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["text","texts","articles","stories"],k)],j,i),A.f(["question","What skill besides memory and confidence can language learning improve?","answer","problem-solving skills","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["problem solving","problem-solving","solving problems","problem solving skills"],k)],j,i),A.f(["question","What kind of world does the text describe today?","answer","a connected world","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["connected","connected world","global world","modern connected world"],k)],j,i)],h)],j,i)})
s($,"b51","aEl",()=>{var q="Different ways people say the same thing in different languages",p="It helps people understand others better",o="Although, While and Whereas",n="ideas, feelings, and culture",m=t.s,l=t.N,k=t.K,j=t.Mq,i=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 2: Different Ways to Say the Same Thing","backButtonText","Back to Unit 1","title","Different Ways to Say the Same Thing","lessonId","unit1_lesson2","unitTitle","Unit 1","completionText",u.v,"inputType","listening","audioPath","assets/audio/unit1_lesson2_audio.mp3","imagePath","assets/images/unit1_lesson2.png","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit1_lesson2_grammar.mp4","input","Welcome to today\u2019s language programme. We are talking about how people around the world say the same thing in different ways.\n\nFor example, in English, people say \u201chello,\u201d although in Spanish people usually say \u201chola.\u201d In France, people say \u201cbonjour,\u201d while in Japan they often say \u201ckonnichiwa.\u201d\n\nFood words are different too. In Britain, people say \u201cchips,\u201d whereas Americans usually say \u201cfries.\u201d Although the words are different, they describe the same food.\n\nPeople also use different expressions to show politeness. In Korea, people often bow slightly while greeting someone, whereas in many English-speaking countries people usually shake hands.\n\nLanguages may sound very different, although they all help people communicate ideas, feelings, and culture. Learning another language can help us understand people from other countries better.\n\nSo next time you hear a new language, remember that people around the world often say the same thing in many different ways!","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the programme?","options",A.b(["Different foods around the world","Why students dislike languages",q,"How to travel to different countries"],m),"answer",q],l,k),A.f(["question","Which example does the presenter use to explain greetings in different languages?","options",A.b(["goodbye","thank you","hello","good night"],m),"answer","hello"],l,k),A.f(["question","What does the presenter say about learning another language?","options",A.b(["It is too difficult for most people",p,"It is only important in schools","It is only useful for travel"],m),"answer",p],l,k)],j),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","programme","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","a radio or television show"],l,l),A.f(["word","describe","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","to say what something is like"],l,l),A.f(["word","expressions","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","words or phrases people use to communicate ideas or feelings"],l,l),A.f(["word","politeness","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","behaviour that shows good manners and respect"],l,l),A.f(["word","greeting","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","saying hello to someone"],l,l),A.f(["word","culture","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the ideas, customs, and way of life of a group of people"],l,l),A.f(["word","different","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","not the same"],l,l),A.f(["word","understand","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","to know the meaning of something"],l,l)],i),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Different countries have different ways of showing ______ to other people.","options",A.b(["programme","describe","politeness","understand"],m),"answer","politeness"],l,k),A.f(["sentence","Teachers use simple examples to help students ______ new ideas.","options",A.b(["culture","greeting","understand","expressions"],m),"answer","understand"],l,k),A.f(["sentence","The television ______ talked about music from around the world.","options",A.b(["communicate","describe","programme","politeness"],m),"answer","programme"],l,k),A.f(["sentence","Smiling and waving are common ways of ______ someone.","options",A.b(["understand","culture","programme","greeting"],m),"answer","greeting"],l,k),A.f(["sentence","People use facial ______ to show emotions such as happiness or surprise.","options",A.b(["communicate","expressions","describe","politeness"],m),"answer","expressions"],l,k),A.f(["sentence","Learning about another country\u2019s ______ can help people respect each other.","options",A.b(["programme","understand","culture","greeting"],m),"answer","culture"],l,k),A.f(["sentence","English has many ______ words that mean the same thing.","options",A.b(["expressions","describe","different","politeness"],m),"answer","different"],l,k),A.f(["sentence","Can you ______ what this word means in English?","options",A.b(["culture","describe","greeting","programme"],m),"answer","describe"],l,k)],j),"grammar",A.f(["title",o,"summary",A.f(["grammarPoint",o,"use","We use these words to compare and contrast ideas.","form","although + clause\nclause + while + clause\nclause + whereas + clause","examples",A.b(["Languages may sound different, although they help people communicate.","In France people say \u201cbonjour,\u201d while in Japan people say \u201ckonnichiwa.\u201d","In Britain people say \u201cchips,\u201d whereas Americans say \u201cfries.\u201d"],m),"remember","These words help us compare different ideas clearly."],l,k),"example",A.f(["sentence","People say \u201chello\u201d in English, ______ people say \u201chola\u201d in Spanish.","answer","while"],l,l),"instruction","Complete each sentence with although, while, or whereas.","practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence","People in many countries speak different languages, ______ they can still communicate online.","answer","although"],l,l),A.f(["sentence","In Britain people drive on the left, ______ in most European countries people drive on the right.","answer","whereas"],l,l),A.f(["sentence","Some teenagers listen to music ______ studying.","answer","while"],l,l),A.f(["sentence","______ online communication is fast, face-to-face conversations are still important.","answer","Although"],l,l),A.f(["sentence","In some cultures people bow when greeting others, ______ in other cultures people shake hands.","answer","whereas"],l,l)],i)],l,k),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","What do people usually say in Spanish instead of \u201chello\u201d?","options",A.b(["bonjour","fries","hola","goodbye"],m),"answer","hola"],l,k),A.f(["question","In France, people often say:","options",A.b(["konnichiwa","hola","thank you","bonjour"],m),"answer","bonjour"],l,k),A.f(["question","What word do Americans usually use instead of \u201cchips\u201d?","options",A.b(["crisps","fries","rice","biscuits"],m),"answer","fries"],l,k),A.f(["question","What do people often do while greeting someone in Korea?","options",A.b(["hug","wave both hands","bow slightly","jump"],m),"answer","bow slightly"],l,k),A.f(["question","According to the programme, languages help people communicate:","options",A.b(["sports and games","weather and traffic","homework answers",n],m),"answer",n],l,k)],j),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","In which country do people say konnichiwa when greeting someone?","answer","Japan","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["Japan"],m)],l,k),A.f(["question","What food do British people call \u201cchips\u201d?","answer","fries","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["french fries","chips"],m)],l,k),A.f(["question","What do people usually do in many English-speaking countries when greeting someone?","answer","shake hands","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["shake hand","handshake","give a handshake"],m)],l,k),A.f(["question","What can learning another language help people understand better?","answer","people from other countries","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["other people","people from different countries","other cultures","different cultures"],m)],l,k),A.f(["question","According to the presenter, what can languages help people communicate besides ideas and culture?","answer","feelings","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["feeling","their feelings","different feelings"],m)],l,k)],j)],l,k)})
s($,"b53","aEn",()=>{var q="How people communicate without words",p="A busy train station",o="Technology is helping people share feelings online",n="misunderstandings",m="Present Continuous",l="They are feeling nervous or impatient",k="To show confidence and interest",j="Emojis, photos, and videos",i="Avoid misunderstandings",h=t.s,g=t.N,f=t.K,e=t.Mq,d=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 3: Communicate Without Words","backButtonText","Back to Unit 1","title","Communicate Without Words","lessonId","unit1_lesson3","unitTitle","Unit 1","completionText",u.v,"inputType","reading","imagePath","assets/images/unit1_lesson3.png","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit1_lesson3_grammar.mp4","input","Have you ever noticed that people are communicating even when they are not speaking? Around the world, people use body language, facial expressions, and gestures every day. In fact, experts say that a large part of communication is non-verbal.\n\nAt a busy train station, for example, people are showing feelings without using words. Some passengers are smiling while they are meeting friends or family members. Others are crossing their arms or looking at their phones because they are feeling nervous or impatient.\n\nIn different countries, gestures can also have different meanings. In some places, people are nodding their heads to say \u201cyes\u201d, while in other cultures the same movement can mean something different. Eye contact is important too. In many Western countries, people are looking directly at each other to show confidence and interest. However, in some cultures, too much eye contact is considered rude.\n\nTechnology is changing communication as well. Teenagers are using emojis, photos, and videos to express emotions online. Although they are not speaking face-to-face, they are still sharing feelings and ideas.\n\nUnderstanding non-verbal communication can help people avoid misunderstandings and communicate more successfully with others.","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the text?","options",A.b(["Different train stations around the world","How technology is changing transport",q,"Why eye contact is dangerous"],h),"answer",q],g,f),A.f(["question","Which example does the text use to show non-verbal communication?","options",A.b(["A sports centre","A school classroom",p,"An airport restaurant"],h),"answer",p],g,f),A.f(["question","What does the writer say about technology and communication?","options",A.b(["Technology is stopping communication",o,"Technology is only useful for adults","Technology is making people forget languages"],h),"answer",o],g,f)],e),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","gesture","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","a movement of the hands or body used to communicate"],g,g),A.f(["word","nervous","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","worried or afraid about something"],g,g),A.f(["word","impatient","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","annoyed because something is taking too long"],g,g),A.f(["word","non-verbal","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","not involving or using words"],g,g),A.f(["word","rude","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","not polite"],g,g),A.f(["word","express","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","to show feelings or ideas"],g,g),A.f(["word",n,"partOfSpeech","n","meaning","situations where people understand something wrongly"],g,g),A.f(["word","emotions","partOfSpeech","adv","meaning","a strong feeling"],g,g)],d),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Ali felt very ______ before speaking in front of the class.","options",A.b(["gesture","confidence","nervous","emotion"],h),"answer","nervous"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Smiling is a friendly ______ that people use in many countries.","options",A.b(["rude","gesture","express","impatient"],h),"answer","gesture"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Some students become ______ when the teacher takes a long time to start the lesson.","options",A.b(["nervous","successfully","impatient","emotion"],h),"answer","impatient"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Love is a powerful ______.","options",A.b(["express","rude",n,"emotion"],h),"answer","emotion"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Looking at your phone while someone is talking can seem ______.","options",A.b(["nervous","express","rude","confidence"],h),"answer","rude"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","People use music, art, and writing to ______ their feelings.","options",A.b(["gesture","impatient","successfully","express"],h),"answer","express"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Shaking hands is an example of ______ communication.","options",A.b([n,"rude","non-verbal","gesture"],h),"answer","non-verbal"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Different cultures can sometimes cause ______ between people.","options",A.b(["successfully","express","nervous",n],h),"answer",n],g,f)],e),"grammar",A.f(["title",m,"summary",A.f(["grammarPoint",m,"use","We use the present continuous for actions and feelings happening now.","form","be + verb-ing","examples",A.b(["People are communicating.","Some passengers are smiling.","Teenagers are using emojis."],h),"remember","Use the correct form of \u201cbe\u201d before the verb ending in -ing."],g,f),"example",A.f(["sentence","People __________ (communicate) online now.","answer","are communicating"],g,g),"instruction","Complete each sentence using the present continuous form.","practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Some passengers __________ (smile).","answer","are smiling"],g,g),A.f(["sentence","People __________ (show) feelings without words.","answer","are showing"],g,g),A.f(["sentence","Teenagers __________ (use) emojis and videos.","answer","are using"],g,g),A.f(["sentence",u.A,"answer","is changing"],g,g),A.f(["sentence","People __________ (look) directly at each other.","answer","are looking"],g,g)],d)],g,f),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","According to the text, experts say that a large part of communication is:","options",A.b(["spoken","written","non-verbal","formal"],h),"answer","non-verbal"],g,f),A.f(["question","Why are some passengers looking at their phones at the train station?","options",A.b(["They are reading the news","They are studying for exams","They are buying food",l],h),"answer",l],g,f),A.f(["question","In many Western countries, why do people make eye contact?","options",A.b(["To show anger","To avoid speaking",k,"To ask for help"],h),"answer",k],g,f),A.f(["question","What are teenagers using to express emotions online?","options",A.b(["Books and letters",j,"Maps and posters","Newspapers and magazines"],h),"answer",j],g,f),A.f(["question","What can understanding non-verbal communication help people do?","options",A.b(["Travel more easily","Learn maths faster",i,"Become famous online"],h),"answer",i],g,f)],e),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What do people use every day besides words to communicate?","answer","Body language, facial expressions, and gestures","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["body language","facial expressions","gestures","body language and gestures","gestures and facial expressions","body language facial expressions and gestures"],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","What are some passengers doing when they meet friends or family members?","answer","Smiling","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["smile","smiling at them","they are smiling"],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","What movement do people often use to say \u201cyes\u201d?","answer","Nodding their heads","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["nod","nodding","nodding their head","nod their heads","nodding heads"],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","In some cultures, too much eye contact is considered what?","answer","Rude","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["impolite","disrespectful"],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","What are teenagers sharing online besides emotions?","answer","Ideas","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["their ideas","thoughts","opinions"],h)],g,f)],e)],g,f)})
s($,"b55","aEp",()=>{var q="How people use technology and communicate online",p="It is becoming more popular",o="People should think carefully about how they use technology",n="It is faster and easier than making phone calls",m="notifications appearing on their screens",l="researching information",k="balancing online and offline activities",j=t.s,i=t.N,h=t.K,g=t.Mq,f=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 4: How People Spend Their Time Online","backButtonText","Back to Unit 1","title","How People Spend Their Time Online","lessonId","unit1_lesson4","unitTitle","Unit 1","completionText",u.v,"inputType","listening","audioPath","assets/audio/unit1_lesson4_audio.mp3","imagePath","assets/images/unit1_lesson4.png","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit1_lesson4_grammar.mp4","input","Welcome to today\u2019s technology programme. We are discussing how people spend their time online and why digital communication is becoming such an important part of everyday life.\n\nMany teenagers enjoy using the internet for different activities. Watching videos, sharing photos, and chatting with friends are some of the most common online habits. For many young people, sending messages is faster and easier than making phone calls.\n\nHowever, spending too much time online can also create problems. Some students dislike studying while notifications are appearing on their screens. Others find it difficult to stop scrolling through social media before going to sleep.\n\nOnline learning is becoming more popular too. Listening to podcasts, joining virtual classes, and researching information are helping students learn in new ways. Some schools are even encouraging students to practise speaking skills by recording videos or participating in online discussions.\n\nAlthough technology offers many advantages, experts believe that balancing online and offline activities is important. Spending time outdoors, exercising regularly, and meeting people face-to-face are still necessary for a healthy lifestyle.\n\nSo next time you go online, think carefully about how you are using technology and whether it is improving your daily life.","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the programme?","options",A.b(["Why students dislike homework",q,"How teenagers play sports","Why schools should ban phones"],j),"answer",q],i,h),A.f(["question","What does the presenter say about online learning?","options",A.b(["It is only useful for adults","It is becoming less common",p,"It is replacing all schools"],j),"answer",p],i,h),A.f(["question","What does the presenter suggest at the end of the programme?","options",A.b(["People should stop using technology completely","People should spend all their time online","Technology should only be used in schools",o],j),"answer",o],i,h)],g),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","habits","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","things that people do regularly"],i,i),A.f(["word","notifications","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","messages or alerts that appear on a phone or computer"],i,i),A.f(["word","scrolling","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","moving up or down on a screen to look at information"],i,i),A.f(["word","virtual","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","happening online instead of in a real place"],i,i),A.f(["word","discussions","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","conversations where people share ideas"],i,i),A.f(["word","advantages","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","good points or benefits of something"],i,i),A.f(["word","balancing","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","keeping different things at a healthy or equal level"],i,i),A.f(["word","lifestyle","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the way a person lives"],i,i)],f),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Eating healthy food and exercising are important parts of a good ______.","options",A.b(["habits","advantages","lifestyle","virtual"],j),"answer","lifestyle"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Many students now attend ______ lessons from home using their computers.","options",A.b(["scrolling","notifications","virtual","discussions"],j),"answer","virtual"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Sofia turned off her phone ______ so she could focus on her homework.","options",A.b(["habits","advantages","lifestyle","notifications"],j),"answer","notifications"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Reading before bed instead of ______ through social media can help people sleep better.","options",A.b(["balancing","virtual","scrolling","discussions"],j),"answer","scrolling"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Teachers often organise class ______ so students can share their opinions.","options",A.b(["notifications","advantages","discussions","habits"],j),"answer","discussions"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Good study ______ can help students improve their grades.","options",A.b(["lifestyle","virtual","scrolling","habits"],j),"answer","habits"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","There are many ______ to learning another language, including travel and work opportunities.","options",A.b(["notifications","balancing","advantages","discussions"],j),"answer","advantages"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","______ schoolwork, hobbies, and rest is important for teenagers.","options",A.b(["Scrolling","Virtual","Balancing","Notifications"],j),"answer","Balancing"],i,h)],g),"grammar",A.f(["title","-ing Forms","summary",A.f(["grammarPoint","-ing Forms","use","We use -ing forms as subjects and after some verbs.","form","-ing form + verb\nverb + -ing form","examples",A.b(["Sending messages is faster than making phone calls.","Many teenagers enjoy using the internet.","Exercising regularly is important for a healthy lifestyle."],j),"remember","An -ing form can work like a noun in a sentence."],i,h),"example",A.f(["sentence","People __________ (watch) videos online every day.","answer","Watching"],i,i),"instruction","Complete each sentence using the correct -ing form.","practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence",u.I,"answer","Sending"],i,i),A.f(["sentence",u.Y,"answer","using"],i,i),A.f(["sentence","Some students dislike __________ (study).","answer","studying"],i,i),A.f(["sentence","Schools are encouraging students to practise speaking by __________ (record) videos.","answer","recording"],i,i),A.f(["sentence","__________ (exercise) regularly is important for a healthy lifestyle.","answer","Exercising"],i,i)],f)],i,h),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","Which activity is mentioned as a common online habit for teenagers?","options",A.b(["writing books","sharing photos","cooking meals","driving cars"],j),"answer","sharing photos"],i,h),A.f(["question","Why do many young people prefer sending messages?","options",A.b(["It helps improve handwriting","It uses less electricity",n,"It avoids using the internet"],j),"answer",n],i,h),A.f(["question","What can make studying difficult for some students?","options",A.b(["watching films","reading books","playing sports",m],j),"answer",m],i,h),A.f(["question","Which activity is helping students learn in new ways?","options",A.b(["shopping online","watching advertisements",l,"playing computer games all night"],j),"answer",l],i,h),A.f(["question","According to experts, what is important for a healthy lifestyle?","options",A.b(["avoiding technology completely",k,"using social media all day","sleeping less often"],j),"answer",k],i,h)],g),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What are many teenagers using to chat with friends?","answer","the internet","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["technology","internet","online platforms","social media","apps"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What is faster and easier than making phone calls?","answer","sending messages","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["messages","texting","sending texts","sending text messages"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What are some students scrolling through before going to sleep?","answer","social media","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["their social media","social media apps","instagram","tiktok"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What are some schools encouraging students to practise by recording?","answer","speaking skills","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["speaking","their speaking","oral skills","communication skills"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What kind of activities should people balance with online activities?","answer","offline activities","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["offline","offline activity","real life activities","activities offline","face-to-face activities"],j)],i,h)],g)],i,h)})
s($,"b57","aEr",()=>{var q="How teenagers communicate and express themselves online",p="It gives teenagers new ways to express ideas and identity",o="Understanding, kindness, and honesty",n="new ways to express themselves",m="discuss important topics",l="confidence and independence",k="because comments can cause misunderstanding or conflict",j="stress or insecurity",i=t.s,h=t.N,g=t.K,f=t.Mq,e=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 5: Sharing Feelings and Ideas Online","backButtonText","Back to Unit 1","title","Sharing Feelings and Ideas Online","lessonId","unit1_lesson5","unitTitle","Unit 1","completionText","You practised reading for gist, useful vocabulary, conjunctions, and comprehension.","inputType","reading","imagePath","assets/images/unit1_lesson5.png","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit1_lesson5_grammar.mp4","input","For teenagers today, communication is about much more than simply sending messages. Social media, videos, and online communities are giving young people new ways to express their thoughts, creativity, and identity.\n\nMany teenagers enjoy the freedom of sharing opinions, photos, and personal experiences online. Platforms such as blogs and video channels allow users to discuss important topics, support different causes, and connect with people who have similar interests. For some students, online communication provides confidence and independence that they may not always feel in face-to-face conversations.\n\nHowever, experts also warn about the importance of responsibility and respect online. A single comment can sometimes cause misunderstanding, embarrassment, or conflict. Because of this, schools are encouraging students to think carefully before posting messages or sharing information publicly.\n\nOnline communication can also influence identity. Teenagers are often exploring different interests, friendships, and communities while they are growing up. Positive online experiences can create happiness, inspiration, and motivation. At the same time, too much pressure from social media may lead to stress or insecurity.\n\nAlthough technology continues to change communication, understanding, kindness, and honesty remain important in every conversation.","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the article?","options",A.b(["How to create video channels online","Why teenagers should avoid the internet",q,"Why schools should stop online communication"],i),"answer",q],h,g),A.f(["question","What does the writer say about online communication for teenagers?","options",A.b(["It only creates problems",p,"It is only useful for adults","It stops teenagers from having interests"],i),"answer",p],h,g),A.f(["question","What does the article suggest is still important in communication?","options",A.b(["Fame and popularity","Speed and technology",o,"Photos and videos"],i),"answer",o],h,g)],f),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","creativity","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the ability to produce new and original ideas"],h,h),A.f(["word","identity","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","who a person is and how they see themselves"],h,h),A.f(["word","opinions","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","a view or judgment about a particular matter"],h,h),A.f(["word","independence","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the ability to do things by yourself"],h,h),A.f(["word","responsibility","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the duty to behave in a sensible way"],h,h),A.f(["word","embarrassment","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the feeling of being ashamed or uncomfortable"],h,h),A.f(["word","inspiration","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","a feeling that gives people new ideas or motivation"],h,h),A.f(["word","insecurity","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","a lack of confidence or feeling unsure about yourself"],h,h)],e),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Drawing, writing stories, and making music can help students develop their ______.","options",A.b(["opinion","identity","creativity","responsibility"],i),"answer","creativity"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Learning to manage homework alone teaches teenagers ______.","options",A.b(["insecurity","embarrassment","inspiration","independence"],i),"answer","independence"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Public speaking can give students the experience of effectively sharing their ______ in groups.","options",A.b(["identity","responsibility","opinion","insecurity"],i),"answer","opinion"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Many young people explore their ______ through fashion, hobbies, and music.","options",A.b(["creativity","embarrassment","identity","inspiration"],i),"answer","identity"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Forgetting your lines during a performance may cause ______.","options",A.b(["opinion","independence","responsibility","embarrassment"],i),"answer","embarrassment"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Teachers want students to show ______ by completing work on time.","options",A.b(["insecurity","identity","creativity","responsibility"],i),"answer","responsibility"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Famous athletes often give young people ______ to work hard and follow their dreams.","options",A.b(["opinion","embarrassment","inspiration","independence"],i),"answer","inspiration"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Comparing yourself to others online can sometimes create feelings of ______.","options",A.b(["identity","responsibility","insecurity","creativity"],i),"answer","insecurity"],h,g)],f),"grammar",A.f(["title","Abstract Nouns","summary",A.f(["grammarPoint","Abstract Nouns","use","We use abstract nouns for ideas, feelings, and qualities.","form","abstract noun","examples",A.b(["Communication is important.","Online communication provides confidence.","Kindness and honesty remain important."],i),"remember","Abstract nouns are usually used without \u201ca/an\u201d or \u201cthe\u201d."],h,g),"example",A.f(["sentence","People need __________ (kind) when communicating online.","answer","kindness"],h,h),"instruction","Complete each sentence using the correct abstract noun.","practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence",u.x,"answer","happiness"],h,h),A.f(["sentence","Teenagers enjoy the __________ (free) of sharing opinions.","answer","freedom"],h,h),A.f(["sentence","Respect and __________ (honest) are important online.","answer","honesty"],h,h),A.f(["sentence","Some online experiences may cause __________ (embarrassed).","answer","embarrassment"],h,h),A.f(["sentence",u.n,"answer","confidence"],h,h)],e)],h,g),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","What are social media and online communities giving young people?","options",A.b(["more homework","fewer friendships",n,"less technology"],i),"answer",n],h,g),A.f(["question","What do blogs and video channels allow users to do?","options",A.b(["avoid communication","stop using social media","travel around the world",m],i),"answer",m],h,g),A.f(["question","What may online communication provide for some students?","options",A.b(["money and success",l,"better eyesight","fewer responsibilities"],i),"answer",l],h,g),A.f(["question","Why are schools encouraging students to think carefully before posting online?","options",A.b(["because technology is expensive","because students dislike computers",k,"because online videos are too long"],i),"answer",k],h,g),A.f(["question","What may too much pressure from social media lead to?","options",A.b(["happiness and motivation","better communication skills",j,"stronger friendships"],i),"answer",j],h,g)],f),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What are many teenagers sharing online besides opinions?","answer","photos and personal experiences","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["photos","personal experiences","pictures and experiences","photos and experiences","personal stories"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What do some students gain from online communication?","answer",l,"acceptedAnswers",A.b(["confidence","independence","more confidence","confidence and freedom"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What can a single comment sometimes cause?","answer","misunderstanding, embarrassment, or conflict","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["misunderstanding","embarrassment","conflict","arguments","problems"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What are teenagers exploring while growing up?","answer","different interests, friendships, and communities","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["interests friendships and communities","different interests","friendships","communities","new interests and friendships"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What should remain important in every conversation?","answer","understanding, kindness, and honesty","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["understanding kindness and honesty","kindness","honesty","respect","being kind and honest"],i)],h,g)],f)],h,g)})
s($,"b50","aEk",()=>{var q="Why everyday objects are important",p="Simple everyday objects people use regularly",o=u.N,n="a bottle of water",m="a slice of bread",l="A piece of paper with homework",k="Study, work, travel, and communicate",j=t.s,i=t.N,h=t.K,g=t.Mq,f=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 1: Everyday Objects","backButtonText","Back to Unit 2","title","Everyday Objects","lessonId","unit2_lesson1","unitTitle","Unit 2","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit2_lesson1_grammar.mp4","completionText",u.O,"inputType","reading","imagePath","assets/images/unit2_lesson1.png","input","When people think about important inventions, they often imagine huge machines or expensive technology. However, many everyday objects quietly make our lives easier and more comfortable.\n\nTake my school bag, for example. Inside it, there is a piece of paper with my homework, a bottle of water, a bar of chocolate for lunch, and a few packets of tissues. These are all simple objects, but I use them every day without thinking very much about them.\n\nAt home, there are also many useful items that help families complete daily tasks. A slice of bread in the morning, a cup of tea after school, or a tube of toothpaste in the bathroom may seem ordinary, but they are part of everyday routines around the world.\n\nSome objects are becoming more environmentally friendly too. Many teenagers are now carrying reusable bottles instead of buying plastic drinks. Others are using bars of soap rather than bottles of liquid soap to reduce waste.\n\nAlthough everyday objects are small, they can have a big effect on people\u2019s lives. A simple tool, a useful container, or even a box of pencils can help people study, work, travel, and communicate more easily every day.","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the blog?","options",A.b(["Expensive modern technology",q,"How to design school bags","Why teenagers dislike routines"],j),"answer",q],i,h),A.f(["question","What examples does the writer mainly discuss in the text?","options",A.b(["Famous inventions and machines","Sports equipment and games",p,"Different kinds of transport"],j),"answer",p],i,h),A.f(["question","What does the writer suggest about some modern objects?","options",A.b([o,"They are becoming more expensive","Teenagers are using fewer objects","People no longer use reusable items"],j),"answer",o],i,h)],g),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","inventions","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","new things or machines that people create"],i,i),A.f(["word","comfortable","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","making you feel relaxed or at ease"],i,i),A.f(["word","ordinary","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","normal or not special"],i,i),A.f(["word","routines","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","regular ways of doing things every day"],i,i),A.f(["word","reusable","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","able to be used again many times"],i,i),A.f(["word","reduce","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","to make something smaller or less"],i,i),A.f(["word","container","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","something used to hold or carry things"],i,i),A.f(["word","waste","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","material that is worthless, defective, or of no use"],i,i)],f),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Bringing your own bag to the shop can help ______ plastic waste.","options",A.b(["reduce","invent","routines","contain"],j),"answer","reduce"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Scientists are always creating new ______ to improve people\u2019s lives.","options",A.b(["inventions","routines","containers","messages"],j),"answer","inventions"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Water bottles and lunch boxes are useful types of ______.","options",A.b(["container","routine","invention","comfort"],j),"answer","container"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Many students follow morning ______ before going to school.","options",A.b(["routines","containers","inventions","ideas"],j),"answer","routines"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Wearing soft clothes can help people feel more ______ during long journeys.","options",A.b(["comfortable","ordinary","reusable","expensive"],j),"answer","comfortable"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Teachers encourage students to reduce the amount of ________ they leave after lunchtimes.","options",A.b(["waste","reduce","carry","invent"],j),"answer","waste"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Using a ______ shopping bag is better for the environment than using plastic bags once.","options",A.b(["reusable","ordinary","comfortable","simple"],j),"answer","reusable"],i,h),A.f(["sentence","Although the caf\xe9 looked very ______, the food was excellent.","options",A.b(["ordinary","waste","reusable","useful"],j),"answer","ordinary"],i,h)],g),"grammar",A.f(["title","Partitives","summary",A.f(["grammarPoint","Partitives","use","We use partitives to talk about quantities and amounts.","form","a/an + partitive + of + noun","examples",A.b([n,m,"a piece of paper"],j),"remember","Different nouns use different partitives."],i,h),"example",A.f(["sentence","I drank __________ of water.","answer","a bottle"],i,i),"instruction","Complete each sentence using the correct partitive.","practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence","She ate __________ of bread.","answer","a slice"],i,i),A.f(["sentence","He bought __________ of chocolate.","answer","a bar"],i,i),A.f(["sentence","We used __________ of toothpaste.","answer","a tube"],i,i),A.f(["sentence","They opened __________ of pencils.","answer","a box"],i,i),A.f(["sentence","I wrote on __________ of paper.","answer","a piece"],i,i)],f)],i,h),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","What is inside the writer\u2019s school bag?","options",A.b(["A laptop and headphones",l,"A football and sports shoes","A library book and a ruler"],j),"answer",l],i,h),A.f(["question","What does the writer drink after school?","options",A.b(["Juice","Coffee","Tea","Milk"],j),"answer","Tea"],i,h),A.f(["question","Why are some teenagers using reusable bottles?","options",A.b(["To save money on school bags","To reduce waste","To carry more drinks","To decorate their rooms"],j),"answer","To reduce waste"],i,h),A.f(["question","What are some people using instead of bottles of liquid soap?","options",A.b(["Bars of soap","Packets of tissues","Tubes of toothpaste","Cups of water"],j),"answer","Bars of soap"],i,h),A.f(["question","According to the text, what can a box of pencils help people do?","options",A.b(["Exercise and cook","Sleep and relax",k,"Clean the house and garden"],j),"answer",k],i,h)],g),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the writer carrying for lunch?","answer","a bar of chocolate","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["bar of chocolate","chocolate","a chocolate bar"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What is the writer bringing for a drink?","answer",n,"acceptedAnswers",A.b(["bottle of water","water","a water"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What does the author eat for breakfast?","answer",m,"acceptedAnswers",A.b(["slice of bread","bread"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What kind of bottles are many teenagers carrying now?","answer","reusable bottles","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["reusable","reusable bottle","water bottles","reusable water bottles"],j)],i,h),A.f(["question","What does the author say can have a big effect on people\u2019s lives?","answer","everyday objects","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["everyday object"],j)],i,h)],g)],i,h)})
s($,"b52","aEm",()=>{var q="What life would be like without everyday objects",p="A world without everyday objects",o="They can make life easier and more comfortable",n="Second Conditional",m="read printed books and write by hand",l="spend more time outdoors",k="They would need to buy fresh food every day",j="small changes in daily habits",i=t.s,h=t.N,g=t.K,f=t.Mq,e=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 2: Imagining Different Worlds","backButtonText","Back to Unit 2","title","Imagining Different Worlds","lessonId","unit2_lesson2","unitTitle","Unit 2","completionText",u.w,"inputType","listening","audioPath","assets/audio/unit2_lesson2_audio.mp3","imagePath","assets/images/unit2_lesson2.png","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit2_lesson2_grammar.mp4","input","Welcome back to the Teen Minds Podcast! Today, we\u2019re imagining a very different world. What would happen if everyday objects suddenly disappeared?\n\nThink about your normal school day. What would you do if you didn\u2019t have a phone, a pen, or even a backpack? Many teenagers say they would feel completely lost. If students didn\u2019t have computers, they would probably spend more time reading printed books or writing by hand.\n\nSome people believe life would become less stressful without technology. If social media didn\u2019t exist, teenagers might spend more time outdoors or talking face-to-face with friends. On the other hand, communication would become much slower. If people couldn\u2019t send instant messages, arranging plans would take much more time.\n\nEveryday objects also make homes more comfortable. If families didn\u2019t have refrigerators, they would need to buy fresh food every day. If washing machines disappeared, people would spend hours cleaning clothes by hand.\n\nOf course, some inventions can create problems too. If people used fewer plastic products, the environment would probably become cleaner. Many scientists believe that small changes in daily habits could improve the future of the planet.\n\nSo, what object could you not live without? And if you could invent something completely new, what would it be?","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the podcast?","options",A.b(["How technology was invented",q,"Why schools need more computers","How to recycle plastic products"],i),"answer",q],h,g),A.f(["question","What does the speaker ask listeners to imagine?","options",A.b(["A future with more robots",p,"A school without teachers","A city without transport"],i),"answer",p],h,g),A.f(["question","What does the podcast suggest about everyday objects?","options",A.b(["They are not very useful",o,"They should all be replaced","Teenagers do not need them"],i),"answer",o],h,g)],f),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","disappeared","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","went away or could not be seen anymore"],h,h),A.f(["word","stressful","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning",u.C],h,h),A.f(["word","suddenly","partOfSpeech","adv","meaning","in a sudden manner; quickly"],h,h),A.f(["word","arranging","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","planning or organising something"],h,h),A.f(["word","refrigerators","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","machines that keep food cold and fresh"],h,h),A.f(["word","instant","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","immediate, direct"],h,h),A.f(["word","environment","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","the natural world around us"],h,h),A.f(["word","fresh","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","not stale, sour, or decayed; new"],h,h)],e),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Many people are trying to protect the ______ by recycling plastic and paper.","options",A.b(["fresh","refrigerators","environment","habits"],i),"answer","environment"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","It is important to include ______ fruit in your diet.","options",A.b(["machines","fresh","arrangements","inventions"],i),"answer","fresh"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Mobile phones have increased ______ communication between friends and families.","options",A.b(["stress","instant","arranging","environment"],i),"answer","instant"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","The lesson became very ______ because students had a test and a homework deadline on the same day.","options",A.b(["comfortable","ordinary","stressful","confident"],i),"answer","stressful"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","She stood up _______ and surprised everyone.","options",A.b(["containers","routines","habits","suddenly"],i),"answer","suddenly"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","My parents are ______ a family trip for the school holidays.","options",A.b(["fresh","arranging","instantly","disappearing"],i),"answer","arranging"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","If all the internet connections suddenly ______, many people would not know what to do.","options",A.b(["instantly","improved","disappeared","arranged"],i),"answer","disappeared"],h,g),A.f(["sentence","Most homes today use ______ to keep food fresh for longer.","options",A.b(["machines","refrigerators","containers","inventions"],i),"answer","refrigerators"],h,g)],f),"grammar",A.f(["title",n,"summary",A.f(["grammarPoint",n,"use","We use the second conditional to imagine unreal or unlikely situations.","form","if + past simple, would + verb","examples",A.b(["If social media didn\u2019t exist, teenagers might spend more time outdoors.","If students didn\u2019t have computers, they would read more books.","If I were you, I wouldn\u2019t travel in this weather."],i),"remember","Use the past simple after \u201cif\u201d and \u201cwould\u201d in the main clause."],h,g),"example",A.f(["sentence","If people __________ (use) fewer plastic products, the environment would become cleaner.","answer","used"],h,h),"instruction","Complete each sentence using the correct second conditional form.","practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence",u.G,"answer","didn\u2019t have"],h,h),A.f(["sentence","If social media __________ (not exist), teenagers might spend more time outdoors.","answer","didn\u2019t exist"],h,h),A.f(["sentence","If people __________ (not send) instant messages, arranging plans would take longer.","answer","couldn\u2019t send"],h,h),A.f(["sentence",u.s,"answer","would clean"],h,h),A.f(["sentence","If I were you, I __________ (not travel) in this weather.","answer","wouldn\u2019t travel"],h,h)],e)],h,g),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","How would many teenagers feel without phones, pens, or backpacks?","options",A.b(["excited","relaxed","completely lost","confident"],i),"answer","completely lost"],h,g),A.f(["question","What would students probably do more often without computers?","options",A.b(["play games",m,"travel to school","watch videos online"],i),"answer",m],h,g),A.f(["question","What might teenagers do more often if social media did not exist?","options",A.b([l,"buy more technology","stay at home alone","use more plastic products"],i),"answer",l],h,g),A.f(["question","What would happen if families did not have refrigerators?","options",A.b(["They would eat less food","They would cook outdoors",k,"They would stop using kitchens"],i),"answer",k],h,g),A.f(["question","According to the text, what could improve the future of the planet?","options",A.b(["using more technology","building larger homes",j,"sending more instant messages"],i),"answer",j],h,g)],f),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What object do many teenagers use for communication every day?","answer","phones","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["phone","mobile phones","smartphones","mobile phone","a phone"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What would communication become without instant messages?","answer","much slower","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["slower","very slow","more difficult and slower"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What household machine helps people clean clothes?","answer","washing machines","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["washing machine","washer","a washing machine"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What kind of products should people use fewer of to help the environment?","answer","plastic products","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["plastic","plastic items","plastic objects","products made of plastic"],i)],h,g),A.f(["question","What do scientists believe small changes could improve?","answer","the future of the planet","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["the planet","the future","the earth","the future of earth","the future of the earth"],i)],h,g)],f)],h,g)})
s($,"b54","aEo",()=>{var q="Incredible buildings and their features",p="Because of their design or history",o=u.N,n="Relative Clauses with Prepositions",m="being the tallest building in the world",l="because of its unique shape",k="special safety systems",j="creativity, culture, and technology",i="the Burj Khalifa",h=t.s,g=t.N,f=t.K,e=t.Mq,d=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 3: Amazing Buildings","backButtonText","Back to Unit 2","title","Amazing Buildings","lessonId","unit2_lesson3","unitTitle","Unit 2","completionText",u.w,"inputType","reading","imagePath","assets/images/unit2_lesson3.png","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit2_lesson3_grammar.mp4","input","Around the world, there are many amazing buildings in which people live, work, and study. Some are famous because of their unusual design, while others are important because of the history with which they are connected.\n\nOne incredible example is the Burj Khalifa in Dubai, which is currently the tallest building in the world. Thousands of visitors travel there every year to enjoy the view from the top floor. Another famous structure is the Sydney Opera House in Sydney, for which architects are admired because of its unique shape.\n\nSome buildings are designed for difficult environments. In countries where earthquakes happen frequently, engineers create structures to which special safety systems are added. These systems help buildings remain stable during strong movement.\n\nModern buildings are also becoming more environmentally friendly. Many architects are now creating homes in which solar panels and recycling systems are included. Some offices even have gardens on their roofs, from which workers can enjoy fresh air during breaks.\n\nAmazing buildings are more than just places to live or work. They reflect the creativity, culture, and technology of the societies from which they come.","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the article?","options",A.b(["Famous cities around the world",q,"How people travel to work","Different types of weather"],h),"answer",q],g,f),A.f(["question","Why are some buildings famous according to the article?","options",A.b(["Because they are very old","Because they are cheap to build",p,"Because they are only used by tourists"],h),"answer",p],g,f),A.f(["question","What does the article say about modern buildings?","options",A.b([o,"They are becoming smaller every year","They are only built in large cities","They are using fewer safety systems"],h),"answer",o],g,f)],e),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","unusual","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","different from what is normal or expected"],g,g),A.f(["word","structure","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","a building or something that has been built"],g,g),A.f(["word","admired","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","respected or liked by many people"],g,g),A.f(["word","earthquakes","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","sudden movements of the ground"],g,g),A.f(["word","stable","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","strong and not likely to fall or change"],g,g),A.f(["word","environmentally","partOfSpeech","adv","meaning","connected to the natural world and protecting it"],g,g),A.f(["word","recycling","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","using materials again instead of throwing them away"],g,g),A.f(["word","reflect","partOfSpeech","v","meaning","to show or represent something"],g,g)],d),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Scientists are studying how buildings can remain ______ during strong storms.","options",A.b(["reflect","stable","admired","recycling"],h),"answer","stable"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Many schools are encouraging ______ to reduce waste and protect the planet.","options",A.b(["earthquakes","unusual","recycling","structure"],h),"answer","recycling"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","The Eiffel Tower is an ______ building because of its famous design.","options",A.b(["environmentally","unusual","stable","reflect"],h),"answer","unusual"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Modern cities are trying to develop more ______ friendly transport systems.","options",A.b(["admired","structure","recycling","environmentally"],h),"answer","environmentally"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Large ______ can damage roads, buildings, and bridges.","options",A.b(["earthquakes","stable","reflect","unusual"],h),"answer","earthquakes"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","The museum is a modern ______ made from glass and steel.","options",A.b(["structure","admired","recycling","environmentally"],h),"answer","structure"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Ancient temples are often ______ for their beauty and history.","options",A.b(["stable","reflect","admired","earthquakes"],h),"answer","admired"],g,f),A.f(["sentence","Traditional buildings often ______ the culture of the country where they were built.","options",A.b(["recycling","reflect","unusual","stable"],h),"answer","reflect"],g,f)],e),"grammar",A.f(["title",n,"summary",A.f(["grammarPoint",n,"use","We use relative clauses with prepositions to describe people, places, and things more clearly.","form","noun + preposition + which + clause","examples",A.b(["Homes in which solar panels are included.","Structures to which safety systems are added.","Gardens from which workers enjoy fresh air."],h),"remember","The preposition comes before \u201cwhich\u201d in formal English."],g,f),"example",A.f(["sentence","Homes __________ solar panels are included can save energy.","answer","in which"],g,g),"instruction",u.F,"practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence",u.c,"answer","in which"],g,g),A.f(["sentence","Structures __________ safety systems are added are safer during emergencies.","answer","to which"],g,g),A.f(["sentence",u.R,"answer","from which"],g,g),A.f(["sentence","The societies __________ these buildings come are very different.","answer","from which"],g,g),A.f(["sentence","The Sydney Opera House is a building __________ architects are admired.","answer","for which"],g,g)],d)],g,f),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the Burj Khalifa famous for?","options",A.b(["being the oldest building in the world",m,"having the largest garden","being built underground"],h),"answer",m],g,f),A.f(["question","Why are architects admired for the Sydney Opera House?","options",A.b([l,"because it is very cheap","because it has many offices","because it is made of wood"],h),"answer",l],g,f),A.f(["question","What do engineers add to buildings in earthquake areas?","options",A.b(["swimming pools","solar panels",k,"glass roofs"],h),"answer",k],g,f),A.f(["question","What can workers enjoy from rooftop gardens?","options",A.b(["free food","fresh air","music performances","sports activities"],h),"answer","fresh air"],g,f),A.f(["question","According to the article, amazing buildings reflect:","options",A.b(["fashion and entertainment","weather and transport",j,"business and tourism only"],h),"answer",j],g,f)],e),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the tallest building in the world called?","answer",i,"acceptedAnswers",A.b(["Burj Khalifa",i],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","What do thousands of visitors enjoy from the top floor of the Burj Khalifa?","answer","the view","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["view","views","the view"],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","What natural event happens frequently in some countries?","answer","earthquakes","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["earthquake","earthquakes"],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","What systems are included in some environmentally friendly homes?","answer","solar panels and recycling systems","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["recyclingsolar panels and recycling systems","recycling systems and solar panels","solar panels","recycling systems"],h)],g,f),A.f(["question","What do some offices have on their roofs?","answer","gardens","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["garden","gardens","rooftop gardens"],h)],g,f)],e)],g,f)})
s($,"b56","aEq",()=>{var q="Designing future cities and buildings",p="They may become cleaner and quieter",o="communication and cooperation",n="Questions Beginning with Prepositions",m="For what purpose should large buildings be used?",l="rooftop gardens and solar panels",k="using electric transport and environmentally friendly technology",j="governments, engineers, and local communities",i="They improve people\u2019s health and happiness",h="systems for collecting rainwater",g="crowded and stressful",f=t.s,e=t.N,d=t.K,c=t.Mq,b=t.SN
return A.f(["appBarTitle","Lesson 4: Building a Better Future","backButtonText","Back to Unit 2","title","Building a Better Future","lessonId","unit2_lesson4","unitTitle","Unit 2","completionText",u.w,"inputType","listening","audioPath","assets/audio/unit2_lesson4_audio.mp3","imagePath","assets/images/unit2_lesson4.png","grammarVideoPath","assets/videos/unit2_lesson4_grammar.mp4","input","Welcome back to Teen World Radio! Today, I\u2019m talking about the future of cities and the kinds of buildings people may live and work in one day.\n\nAround the world, architects are designing smarter and greener buildings. Many future homes may include rooftop gardens, solar panels, and systems for collecting rainwater. Experts believe that cities could become cleaner and quieter if more people begin using electric transport and environmentally friendly technology.\n\nHowever, building future cities is not always simple. Governments, engineers, and local communities must make important decisions together. For what purpose should large buildings be used? In which areas should new houses be built? With whom should city planners discuss these ideas before construction begins?\n\nMany people also believe that future cities should include more public spaces. Parks, sports centres, and community gardens can improve people\u2019s health and happiness. Without these areas, cities may feel crowded and stressful, especially for young people.\n\nSome scientists are even developing \u201csmart buildings\u201d in which lights, temperature, and security systems are controlled automatically by computers. These buildings could reduce energy use and make daily life more convenient.\n\nAlthough technology is changing rapidly, communication and cooperation will remain essential for creating better cities in the future.\n\nThanks for listening to Teen World Radio!","inputQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What is the main topic of the radio show?","options",A.b(["Famous buildings from the past",q,"Different kinds of transport today","Problems with modern schools"],f),"answer",q],e,d),A.f(["question","What does the presenter say about future cities?","options",A.b([p,"They will have fewer buildings","They will not use technology","They will become smaller"],f),"answer",p],e,d),A.f(["question","What does the presenter say will remain essential in the future?","options",A.b(["tourism and entertainment",o,"shopping and transport","history and culture"],f),"answer",o],e,d)],c),"vocabulary",A.b([A.f(["word","architects","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","people who design buildings"],e,e),A.f(["word","communities","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","groups of people living in the same area"],e,e),A.f(["word","crowded","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","full of too many people"],e,e),A.f(["word","stressful","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning",u.C],e,e),A.f(["word","security","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","protection from danger or crime"],e,e),A.f(["word","automatically","partOfSpeech","adv","meaning","happening by itself without people controlling it"],e,e),A.f(["word","convenient","partOfSpeech","adj","meaning","easy and useful for people"],e,e),A.f(["word","cooperation","partOfSpeech","n","meaning","working together with others"],e,e)],b),"vocabularyQuestions",A.b([A.f(["sentence","Many modern doors open ______ when a person walks towards them.","options",A.b(["crowded","automatically","convenient","cooperation"],f),"answer","automatically"],e,d),A.f(["sentence","Good ______ between countries can help solve global problems.","options",A.b(["architects","security","cooperation","stressful"],f),"answer","cooperation"],e,d),A.f(["sentence","The shopping centre becomes very ______ on weekends because so many people visit it.","options",A.b(["crowded","convenient","automatically","communities"],f),"answer","crowded"],e,d),A.f(["sentence","Online banking is very ______ because people can use it from home.","options",A.b(["stressful","communities","convenient","architects"],f),"answer","convenient"],e,d),A.f(["sentence","Police officers help provide ______ in cities and public places.","options",A.b(["cooperation","security","crowded","automatically"],f),"answer","security"],e,d),A.f(["sentence","Too much homework and lack of sleep can make school life very ______.","options",A.b(["convenient","stressful","communities","security"],f),"answer","stressful"],e,d),A.f(["sentence","______ often design environmentally friendly buildings for modern cities.","options",A.b(["Architects","Cooperation","Security","Communities"],f),"answer","Architects"],e,d),A.f(["sentence","Local ______ sometimes work together to improve parks and public spaces.","options",A.b(["stressful","convenient","communities","automatically"],f),"answer","communities"],e,d)],c),"grammar",A.f(["title",n,"summary",A.f(["grammarPoint",n,"use","We use prepositions at the beginning of questions to make them clearer and more formal.","form","preposition + which/whom/what + clause","examples",A.b(["In which areas should new houses be built?","With whom should city planners discuss these ideas?",m],f),"remember","Formal questions often begin with a preposition."],e,d),"example",A.f(["sentence","Large buildings should be used for community activities.","answer",m],e,e),"instruction",u.l,"practice",A.b([A.f(["sentence",u.b,"question",u.M,"answer","areas"],e,e),A.f(["sentence",u._,"question",u.L,"answer","whom"],e,e),A.f(["sentence",u.f,"question",u.J,"answer","what"],e,e),A.f(["sentence","\u2192 In which __________ are systems controlled automatically?","question","Smart systems are controlled automatically in modern buildings.","answer","buildings"],e,e),A.f(["sentence",u.u,"question",u.X,"answer","gardens"],e,e)],b)],e,d),"comprehension",A.b([A.f(["question","What may many future homes include?","options",A.b(["underground tunnels",l,"swimming pools and cinemas","factories and offices"],f),"answer",l],e,d),A.f(["question","What could help cities become cleaner and quieter?","options",A.b(["using more plastic products","building taller houses",k,"creating more roads"],f),"answer",k],e,d),A.f(["question","Who must make important decisions together when building future cities?","options",A.b(["tourists and students","teachers and doctors",j,"architects and shopkeepers"],f),"answer",j],e,d),A.f(["question","Why do many people want more public spaces in cities?","options",A.b([i,"They reduce the number of buildings","They create more traffic","They make cities more expensive"],f),"answer",i],e,d),A.f(["question","What are smart buildings using to control lights and temperature automatically?","options",A.b(["robots","computers","phones","cameras"],f),"answer","computers"],e,d)],c),"shortAnswerQuestions",A.b([A.f(["question","What kind of gardens may future homes include?","answer","rooftop gardens","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["rooftop","rooftop gardens","roof gardens","gardens on rooftops"],f)],e,d),A.f(["question","What system may future homes use to collect water?","answer",h,"acceptedAnswers",A.b([h,"rainwater collection systems","rainwater systems","rainwater collection"],f)],e,d),A.f(["question","What may cities feel like without public spaces?","answer",g,"acceptedAnswers",A.b([g,"stressful and crowded","crowded","stressful"],f)],e,d),A.f(["question","What could smart buildings reduce?","answer","energy use","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["energy use","energy consumption","the use of energy"],f)],e,d),A.f(["question","What is changing rapidly according to the presenter?","answer","technology","acceptedAnswers",A.b(["technology"],f)],e,d)],c)],e,d)})
